Qualifications:
1. a Ph.D. or DBA in accounting from an AACSB accredited university (or equivalent). Candidates who expect to complete the degree prior to the positions start date will be considered;
2. a demonstrated ability or potential for excellence in accounting scholarship commensurate with experience;
3. a demonstrated ability or potential for excellence in teaching.

1. Applicants must have a Ph.D. (in marketing or a related field) from an AACSB-accredited business school or expect to complete this degree prior to the positions start date.
2. Successful candidates must a) have expertise in consumer behavior;
3. b) demonstrate evidence, or clear potential, for developing a cohesive and impactful research program;
4. c) be actively engaged in publishing research in top consumer psychology and/or marketing journals;
5. d) show potential for excellence in teaching consumer behavior at the undergraduate and graduate levels.

1. Doctorate in Education, Counseling, Communicative Disorders, Child Development, Information Sciences, Learning Sciences, Educational Technology or a related field by the time of start of position;
